If you are looking for a refreshing drink, Guava and pineapple smoothie might be a great healthy and nutritious option. It is super easy to make, ready in just about 5 minutes. And it's bursting with fibers and antioxidants, making it a great addition to your breakfast. Store this guava smoothie in the fridge in tight seal bottles or jars for up to two days. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Pour a half a cup of coconut milk in a blender and add your peeled pineapple and guavas Step 2 Blend for five minutes until desired. Refrigerate and serve cold.